WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.760
I've had another complaint. And it's
a GMC one. It's going to tribunal.

00:04.760 --> 00:07.200
Why would Erika complain again?
She hasn't. It's anonymous.

00:07.200 --> 00:10.080
You think that you are
the cleverest person in the room,

00:10.080 --> 00:12.600
and that makes you dangerous.
You're a liability!

00:12.600 --> 00:14.800
I mean, I guess you are the one
who sent her home early

00:14.800 --> 00:17.160
and then falsified the notes.
All right, Judge Judy!

00:17.160 --> 00:19.760
If you ever want to chat about
Harry, you know I'm here for you.

00:19.760 --> 00:22.440
I think I'm actually designed
to be on my own.

00:22.440 --> 00:24.720
I'm sorry. I really did try.

00:24.720 --> 00:27.000
SOBS:  I don't know
what she was thinking.

00:36.760 --> 00:38.880
LOUD GROANING

00:38.880 --> 00:42.400
Sorry you've ended up with a twin
room. No room at the inn today.

00:42.400 --> 00:43.840
Better than a bunk bed, I guess.

00:43.840 --> 00:46.040
Yeah - get four to a room that way!

00:46.040 --> 00:48.000
GROANING, DEVICE BEEPS AND VIBRATES

00:49.520 --> 00:51.960
Sorry! Sorry about the room.

00:51.960 --> 00:53.600
SCREAMING CONTINUES

00:53.600 --> 00:54.760
Sorry.

00:59.120 --> 01:00.840
BABY CRIES

01:00.840 --> 01:02.760
BEEPING AND VIBRATING

01:02.760 --> 01:05.680
Hey, baby! HE LAUGHS

01:05.680 --> 01:08.480
I'm so sorry about all this.

01:08.480 --> 01:12.120
He got wasted at the office party.
I'm going to strangle him later.

01:12.120 --> 01:15.120
Make sure you do a thorough job -
because they're really busy in A&E.

01:15.120 --> 01:18.520
That's a nice big contraction now.
One last big push for me.

01:18.520 --> 01:19.800
You're doing really well.

01:19.800 --> 01:21.920
SHE GROANS

01:21.920 --> 01:23.680
Stop pushing. Pant.

01:23.680 --> 01:25.560
SHE PANTS, MAN LAUGHS

01:27.000 --> 01:28.400
BABY CRIES

01:28.400 --> 01:30.760
Yay! Wahey!

01:32.960 --> 01:34.160
Love you!

01:35.240 --> 01:36.720
Love you.

01:51.640 --> 01:52.920
LIQUID SPLASHES

01:52.920 --> 01:54.320
Sir!

01:54.320 --> 01:56.080
Sir! Stop that.

01:56.080 --> 01:58.160
This is not a toilet,
you absolute...

01:58.160 --> 02:00.400
SHE SHOUTS

02:06.240 --> 02:08.720
Why don't you pop downstairs
and go for a walk for half an hour?

02:08.720 --> 02:11.280
What, you can't squeeze us in
before then?

02:11.280 --> 02:13.200
I'm not running
a Pizza Express, sir.

02:13.200 --> 02:16.040
Who bleeped me?
Tracy needs an FBS done, love.

02:16.040 --> 02:17.960
Do me an FBS.

02:17.960 --> 02:21.960
What does FBS mean?
Foetal blood sample.  Oh.

02:21.960 --> 02:24.320
Which room?  Five. Erm...

02:24.320 --> 02:26.640
Are you going to go to
Shruti's thing later?

02:26.640 --> 02:29.280
Well, I was planning to, but I'm not
sure I can leave all this with a

02:29.280 --> 02:31.200
PE teacher in scrubs.

02:31.200 --> 02:34.400
Er, Adam, can I ask you a question
about a patient I've just seen?

02:34.400 --> 02:39.040
Quick, then.  So...she's
32 and a half years old,

02:39.040 --> 02:41.720
she's 37 weeks pregnant,
generally fit and well.

02:41.720 --> 02:43.360
She has asthma, so sometimes...

02:43.360 --> 02:45.880
Quick's the one
when you get to the fucking point.

02:47.280 --> 02:50.440
Right. She's got a urine infection,
so...  Yeah, erm...

02:51.760 --> 02:54.320
So, should I give her
some antibiotics?

02:54.320 --> 02:57.560
As opposed to what, a healing
crystal and some magic runes?

02:58.760 --> 03:00.360
Absolute waste of organs.

03:00.360 --> 03:03.400
And the award for Boss of the Year
goes to...!

03:05.640 --> 03:08.080
MOBILE VIBRATES

03:13.680 --> 03:15.400
Angle the lamp a bit better for me.

03:17.920 --> 03:18.960
Please?

03:20.960 --> 03:22.000
Please.

03:24.800 --> 03:27.560
Remember to file another complaint
about my manners.

03:27.560 --> 03:29.360
I've had weeks of this now, Adam.

03:29.360 --> 03:32.320
Can you stop being quite so much
of a twat.  Tracy!

03:32.320 --> 03:35.200
No, don't "Tracy" me!
Anyway, the patient's deaf.

03:35.200 --> 03:37.360
And if she wasn't sure,
I'm sure she'd agree

03:37.360 --> 03:39.680
that was a pretty twat-ish thing
to say.

03:39.680 --> 03:41.200
I know old habits
are hard to change,

03:41.200 --> 03:43.120
but want to try being professional?

03:43.120 --> 03:44.720
What, like you?

03:44.720 --> 03:46.720
Well, that's assuming
I still have a profession

03:46.720 --> 03:48.400
after my hearing tomorrow.

03:50.080 --> 03:51.680
SHE SIGHS

03:51.680 --> 03:54.560
And just so you know, I'm nipping
out to Shruti's memorial

03:54.560 --> 03:57.400
for five minutes, if I can.  What,
so you've got time for her

03:57.400 --> 03:58.840
now she's dead, do you?

04:01.320 --> 04:03.200
I'm...sorry. I didn't mean that.

04:05.080 --> 04:07.960
Absolutely sure that it's me
that's the twat?

04:07.960 --> 04:10.360
You do know I can lip-read, right?

04:14.880 --> 04:15.920
Hey.

04:17.360 --> 04:19.320
You coming to the memorial?

04:19.320 --> 04:20.600
Yeah.

04:21.600 --> 04:23.880
BEEPING AND VIBRATING

04:27.760 --> 04:29.560
Have fun.  Hey, give me that.

04:30.920 --> 04:32.520
She'd have wanted you there.

04:34.560 --> 04:37.200
You sure?  Of course.

04:40.640 --> 04:43.080
MOBILE VIBRATES

04:43.080 --> 04:44.440
You've got 30 seconds.

04:44.440 --> 04:47.600
Right. So Emma's been getting
this weird pain in her groin.

04:47.600 --> 04:50.160
It only happens if she stands
on one leg, but it's agony.

04:50.160 --> 04:52.360
What do you reckon?
Stand on two legs.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.160
I mean, if she's putting
her trousers on.

04:54.160 --> 04:56.240
It's probably just
symphysis pubis dysfunction.

04:56.240 --> 04:58.000
It's nothing to worry about.
See a physio.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.680
They can give her this special belt
thing.  You're a legend, and...

05:00.680 --> 05:01.720
Time's up! Bye.

05:06.520 --> 05:09.120
CHATTER

05:09.120 --> 05:10.920
WOMAN CLEARS THROAT

05:10.920 --> 05:14.160
Thanks so much to so many of you
for coming.

05:14.160 --> 05:16.400
Christ knows who's looking
after the labour ward.

05:16.400 --> 05:18.040
Better not be me! MOBILE RINGS

05:18.040 --> 05:21.400
We're obviously here to remember
Shruti Akarya

05:21.400 --> 05:24.080
and to unveil this lovely...

05:25.240 --> 05:28.240
..I'm going to say oak tree
in her honour.

05:29.400 --> 05:33.200
So let me hand over, first of all,
to Mr and Mrs Akarya.

05:33.200 --> 05:36.200
Acharya.  Acharya.

05:38.680 --> 05:40.680
Thank you, all, for coming.

05:42.760 --> 05:45.280
You know, Shruti loved
being a doctor.

05:46.360 --> 05:48.720
But every time she called us,
she would tell us how much

05:48.720 --> 05:51.120
she enjoyed working with you all.

05:53.040 --> 05:59.280
Shruti...brought us huge pride
in everything she achieved.

05:59.280 --> 06:03.760
And it brings us great joy
that she will live on,

06:03.760 --> 06:07.400
not just in our hearts
and our minds,

06:07.400 --> 06:12.840
but in this beautiful tree which
will live longer than anyone here.

06:15.640 --> 06:17.720
APPLAUSE

06:19.480 --> 06:22.120
As Shruti's educational supervisor,

06:22.120 --> 06:26.800
I know first-hand what a committed
and dedicated doctor she was,

06:26.800 --> 06:31.360
as evidenced by her passing
her Part One exam first-time -

06:31.360 --> 06:33.960
something, I might add,
I did not do.

06:33.960 --> 06:36.360
Seven driving tests, too,
and counting.

06:36.360 --> 06:38.800
Can do a caesarean in five minutes
with one hand,

06:38.800 --> 06:40.640
can't reverse around
a bloody corner!

06:40.640 --> 06:42.720
SUBDUED LAUGHTER

06:42.720 --> 06:45.160
We're all the poorer for her loss.

06:46.560 --> 06:51.560
But depression is cruel,
and in Shruti's case, silent.

06:52.920 --> 06:54.240
While she was...

06:56.360 --> 06:58.120
..clearly doing well at work,

06:58.120 --> 07:01.000
obviously, there were other forces
at play.

07:01.000 --> 07:04.360
In life, like on labour ward,
you never really know

07:04.360 --> 07:06.120
what's around the corner.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.000
SHE GROANS

07:11.320 --> 07:13.200
Miss Houghton?  All right?

07:13.200 --> 07:16.520
I think maybe Shruti wasn't quite
as happy at work as you said.

07:17.680 --> 07:19.880
SARCASTICALLY:  No? Do you reckon?

07:19.880 --> 07:23.360
Well, what did you want her parents
to hear, that she couldn't hack it?

07:24.880 --> 07:27.960
I mean, like, shouldn't there be
some kind of investigation?

07:27.960 --> 07:31.160
Or are we all just going to
keep pretending

07:31.160 --> 07:33.600
there's nothing wrong
with this place?

07:33.600 --> 07:36.760
Sorry, I must be dementing. When
did I say there was nothing wrong?

07:36.760 --> 07:40.560
This hospital's got about three
doctors and a budget of £12.50.

07:40.560 --> 07:43.080
So, if you want to change it,
become a government minister,

07:43.080 --> 07:45.920
because there is bollocks-all
any of us here can do.

07:45.920 --> 07:47.760
Well, I...

07:50.120 --> 07:51.560
So what do we do now, then?

07:51.560 --> 07:53.840
Well, we all toddle off back
to work, don't we?

07:55.480 --> 07:59.240
And eventually they forget to water
the tree and that dies as well.

08:08.960 --> 08:11.200
MOBILE VIBRATES

08:18.800 --> 08:20.600
I'm so sorry for your loss.

08:23.280 --> 08:26.000
Er... Did you work closely
with Shruti?

08:27.320 --> 08:28.400
I...

08:30.400 --> 08:32.480
No, not really, no. Erm...

08:36.000 --> 08:37.640
But she's much missed.

08:46.160 --> 08:47.640
Walk with me, Kay.

08:50.640 --> 08:54.600
So...tomorrow's your big day
at GMC towers?

08:55.800 --> 08:57.640
Yes, yeah. It is, yeah.

08:57.640 --> 09:00.280
I must say, I'm very sorry
you're going through all this.

09:00.280 --> 09:02.320
For what it's worth,
I think it's bloody unfair

09:02.320 --> 09:04.920
that it has to end like this.
I'm not sure it's going to end.

09:06.120 --> 09:09.600
Well, you falsified the notes.
Seemed pretty cut-and-dry to me.

09:09.600 --> 09:12.000
I'm not sure anyone really
comes back from that.

09:12.000 --> 09:13.960
No, I wrote what you told me
to write,

09:13.960 --> 09:15.440
and then you weaselled back on it.

09:15.440 --> 09:18.240
Well, my lawyer thinks
I stand a fighting chance.

09:19.680 --> 09:22.160
How are you intending to play things
at the tribunal?

09:23.640 --> 09:27.480
Well, hopefully I'll persuade them
that a simple lapse

09:27.480 --> 09:30.520
in my professional judgment
shouldn't need to bring

09:30.520 --> 09:32.480
my future into question.

09:32.480 --> 09:34.440
You're a bloody good doctor, Adam.

09:35.440 --> 09:37.880
We need more doctors like you.

09:37.880 --> 09:41.360
You owe it to yourself, to your
patients, to stay in the game.

09:41.360 --> 09:46.320
If I was in your position, I think
I'd try and realign the narrative

09:46.320 --> 09:48.440
ever so slightly.

09:48.440 --> 09:50.880
I'm not sure that I follow.

09:50.880 --> 09:56.040
Well, you just tell our friends
at the GMC that your colleague,

09:56.040 --> 10:00.160
Dr Acharya, mistakenly told you
that I said it was OK

10:00.160 --> 10:04.560
to send the patient home when,
in fact, she hadn't spoken to me.

10:06.000 --> 10:10.040
She and she alone knocked over
the first domino.

10:11.880 --> 10:15.080
But she... But she didn't do that.

10:15.080 --> 10:16.120
Who's to know?

10:19.280 --> 10:21.480
You're suggesting
that I throw her...

10:21.480 --> 10:23.360
..I throw Shruti under the bus?

10:23.360 --> 10:25.160
No-one loses this way.

10:25.160 --> 10:28.520
It's time for pragmatism, Adam,
not emotions -

10:28.520 --> 10:31.240
if you want to keep your job,
that is.

10:32.640 --> 10:34.560
ENGINE STARTS

10:37.960 --> 10:40.160
PIANO PLAYS SOFTLY

10:46.880 --> 10:48.960
I've got a crowbar!

10:48.960 --> 10:50.280
Just me, Mum.

10:51.520 --> 10:54.120
I know it's just you.
I've come to smash up the piano.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.920
Schubert.

10:57.920 --> 11:00.120
You'd never know
just from listening.

11:02.880 --> 11:05.200
You all set for tomorrow?

11:05.200 --> 11:09.960
Yeah, I guess.  It's just a hiccup.
It's a vexatious bit of bureaucracy.

11:11.000 --> 11:13.160
You are going to shave, right?
Mm-hm.

11:13.160 --> 11:15.320
Make sure you give
a good showing, Adam,

11:15.320 --> 11:18.960
because we've all worked so hard
to get you here.

11:18.960 --> 11:20.440
Oh, "we", is it?

11:20.440 --> 11:23.240
Remind me how many
labour ward shifts you've done.

11:23.240 --> 11:25.160
Oh, just the one visit
to a labour ward,

11:25.160 --> 11:28.080
and then an entire lifetime given up
to getting you here.

11:30.080 --> 11:32.840
Not sure I remember
ever asking you to.

11:32.840 --> 11:35.440
Quite how you ended up so rude,
I'll never know.

11:38.640 --> 11:40.320
A mystery for the ages.

11:55.560 --> 11:58.040
TANNOY:  We are now approaching
Manchester Piccadilly,

11:58.040 --> 11:59.960
where this service terminates.

12:00.960 --> 12:03.400
Yeah, so I just say yes or no
to their questions.

12:03.400 --> 12:07.000
And anything that needs a longer
answer than that, I'll take it.

12:10.560 --> 12:12.760
Am I going to be all right?

12:12.760 --> 12:14.200
Yeah, totally.

12:17.600 --> 12:19.960
Oh, sorry, hang on. What did he say?

12:19.960 --> 12:22.680
Am I going to be all right?
Oh, Christ knows.

12:23.720 --> 12:26.360
But... But you know my motto -

12:26.360 --> 12:28.160
never say never.

12:30.040 --> 12:32.320
I'm going to go to the bathroom.  OK.

12:34.360 --> 12:36.400
You've got five minutes, Alan.

12:36.400 --> 12:38.320
DOOR BANGS

12:45.200 --> 12:47.040
DOOR OPENS

12:50.600 --> 12:51.920
Just do it.

12:53.160 --> 12:55.040
You treated me like shit
when I was alive.

12:55.040 --> 12:56.640
What does one more time matter?

13:16.400 --> 13:18.120
You weren't doing coke in there?

13:20.280 --> 13:21.480
No.

13:22.840 --> 13:24.400
Adam Kay?

13:29.520 --> 13:32.520
Right, after you. Good luck.

13:37.440 --> 13:39.400
Hope you saved some for us
afterwards.

13:48.280 --> 13:50.880
Great. I'm going to get struck off
in a room that looks like

13:50.880 --> 13:52.880
it's used
for a speed-awareness course.

13:56.680 --> 13:59.560
Good afternoon.
My name is Tina Sharpehouse,

13:59.560 --> 14:01.440
and I'm the tribunal chair.

14:01.440 --> 14:05.480
This is a fitness to practise
hearing for Adam Richard Kay.

14:06.760 --> 14:08.840
Would you please stand up, Dr Kay?

14:09.880 --> 14:12.680
Still calling me "doctor" -
that's a good start.

14:12.680 --> 14:14.880
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth

14:14.880 --> 14:16.560
and nothing but the truth?

14:22.760 --> 14:24.160
I do.

14:24.160 --> 14:25.520
Please be seated.

14:27.760 --> 14:34.600
On April 16th, at 4.15pm, you
reviewed patient Erika Van Hegan,

14:34.600 --> 14:38.240
25 weeks pregnant
and presenting with a headache.

14:38.240 --> 14:40.280
You discharged her home.

14:40.280 --> 14:43.840
You wrote in the notes
that you had discussed this decision

14:43.840 --> 14:46.680
with your consultant,
Mr Nigel Lockhart,

14:46.680 --> 14:48.360
a fact that he denies.

14:48.360 --> 14:50.560
I'd like to say a few words.
WHISPERS:  No, you wouldn't!

14:50.560 --> 14:53.240
There's time for you to say anything
you need to later on.

14:53.240 --> 14:55.440
You may sit back down.
On the day in question,

14:55.440 --> 14:58.600
I was working alongside
an SHO colleague...

15:02.240 --> 15:04.040
..called Shruti Acharya.

15:10.160 --> 15:12.440
HE CHUCKLES I did not see that coming.

15:12.440 --> 15:14.920
I mean, if you'd asked me before,
I'd have said you were toast,

15:14.920 --> 15:18.280
but then - bam, out of nowhere -
you come out with that.

15:18.280 --> 15:20.040
I literally can't believe we won.

15:21.200 --> 15:23.240
I can't tell you how much
I needed this, by the way.

15:23.240 --> 15:25.760
My numbers have NOT been good
this year.

15:32.280 --> 15:34.480
PHONE VIBRATES

16:12.080 --> 16:13.600
Good to see you.

16:13.600 --> 16:16.320
You too.
Do you want...something?

16:16.320 --> 16:17.800
No, thanks.

16:20.080 --> 16:21.480
How are you?

16:21.480 --> 16:23.040
Yeah, not bad.

16:23.040 --> 16:24.680
That's good.

16:24.680 --> 16:26.600
The couple downstairs
have a new baby,

16:26.600 --> 16:30.960
which screams, like, 20 hours a day,
so your timing was pretty good.

16:30.960 --> 16:32.920
HE LAUGHS

16:34.440 --> 16:35.920
You're looking well.

16:35.920 --> 16:37.720
Does that mean fat?

16:37.720 --> 16:40.480
BOTH LAUGH It's her cooking. It's...

16:40.480 --> 16:42.960
You know, the main ingredient
is butter.

16:45.200 --> 16:46.960
How is it?

16:46.960 --> 16:49.640
Attached back to Mummy's
apron strings?

16:49.640 --> 16:51.240
They're slightly strangling.

16:52.440 --> 16:54.120
But, you know,

16:54.120 --> 16:56.960
when did a bit of light
strangulation ever hurt anyone?

17:03.440 --> 17:06.400
So, I had a good chat
with the estate agents.

17:06.400 --> 17:08.760
They said there's actually
a six-month break clause,

17:08.760 --> 17:10.360
so I can move out in September.

17:11.440 --> 17:13.280
I printed off the form.

17:13.280 --> 17:16.080
You just need to sign at the bottom.

17:23.160 --> 17:24.400
How's work?

17:24.400 --> 17:26.600
HE CRIES

17:29.160 --> 17:30.480
Shit.

17:37.240 --> 17:38.520
Shruti?

17:40.200 --> 17:42.080
It's so horrible.

17:44.080 --> 17:46.920
I just keep playing over in my mind
everything I said to her.

17:52.400 --> 17:54.520
Everything I should have said.

17:58.000 --> 18:00.680
Everything I shouldn't. I just...

18:00.680 --> 18:02.840
..I don't understand how it...

18:04.720 --> 18:06.200
Anyway.

18:07.840 --> 18:09.320
I let her down so terribly.

18:10.360 --> 18:12.000
Don't beat yourself up.

18:13.840 --> 18:15.520
I'm sure you were a great boss.

18:15.520 --> 18:17.440
I was a crap boss.

18:19.040 --> 18:20.840
Crap boyfriend. Crap doctor.

18:22.880 --> 18:24.080
Hey, come on.

18:25.520 --> 18:28.040
So, what,
I was an amazing boyfriend?

18:35.440 --> 18:37.240
What are you doing Saturday?

18:37.240 --> 18:38.520
A 10K.

18:39.520 --> 18:40.840
That sounds awful.

18:42.040 --> 18:45.120
Well, there's still a place
at Greg's wedding if you fancy it.

18:46.280 --> 18:47.880
And that's meant to be an upgrade?

18:50.880 --> 18:54.400
Emma's designed the table
decorations. They're terrible.

18:54.400 --> 18:57.080
Like 4ft foot glass dildos.  Christ.

18:59.600 --> 19:01.040
Anyway,

19:01.040 --> 19:04.520
would you consider being
my temporary plus-one?

19:06.000 --> 19:08.120
Oh, I don't know. I don't...
I'm not sure.

19:08.120 --> 19:09.280
Special...

19:10.600 --> 19:13.200
..one-night-only cameo appearance?

19:19.600 --> 19:22.200
PHONE VIBRATES

19:22.200 --> 19:24.320
Hi, Greg.
Quick one - sure it's nothing.

19:24.320 --> 19:25.760
Then, maybe don't phone me about it.

19:25.760 --> 19:27.880
Emma just called to say
the baby's not been kicking.

19:27.880 --> 19:30.520
You know, it's normally a right
little Ronaldo, but this morning

19:30.520 --> 19:33.760
it's more of a Ronny Rosenthal.
More homosexual references, please.

19:33.760 --> 19:36.120
Footwork of Bob Fosse,
that kind of thing.

19:36.120 --> 19:39.040
When did she last feel any movement?
About 90 minutes ago.

19:39.040 --> 19:41.520
Tell her to drink a pint
of ice-cold water.

19:41.520 --> 19:42.840
Should get it moving.

19:42.840 --> 19:45.440
Bit like chucking a pint of cold
