You can't do that.

37:27.240 --> 37:29.640
Don't worry. I'll go and get it.

37:36.440 --> 37:39.040
Woo!  What are you doing?

37:39.040 --> 37:41.120
Woo! Come on, Grandad.

37:47.200 --> 37:48.800
Jesus!

37:48.800 --> 37:51.520
Oh, this is cold. HE CHUCKLES

37:51.520 --> 37:54.000
Oh, God.

37:54.000 --> 37:56.600
Oh, oh, oh, oh.

37:56.600 --> 37:58.520
It's fresh.

37:58.520 --> 38:00.560
THEY LAUGH

38:03.640 --> 38:04.880
Go on, then.

38:07.200 --> 38:08.920
What would your ideal wedding be?

38:11.200 --> 38:13.200
Heated lake.

38:13.200 --> 38:15.680
Obviously.  Obviously.

38:15.680 --> 38:18.920
And otherwise, the same as yours.

38:22.320 --> 38:24.200
Because I'd be marrying you.

38:30.240 --> 38:31.760
Adam...

38:33.960 --> 38:35.680
Tell me we weren't good together.

38:37.960 --> 38:41.720
We were good,
but we were also quite bad.

38:41.720 --> 38:44.160
But the bad stuff was...

38:46.400 --> 38:48.000
..that was all to do with my job.

38:50.760 --> 38:53.040
You know,
medicine is not good for me.

38:54.720 --> 38:56.240
It's, um...

38:57.720 --> 38:59.600
..it's ruined my life.

39:00.600 --> 39:02.400
And it destroyed us.

39:02.400 --> 39:03.960
I don't think it was...

39:05.000 --> 39:06.240
..that simple.

39:08.000 --> 39:12.320
I'd like to say a few words.
Dr Kay, you may sit back down.

39:12.320 --> 39:14.080
On the day in question,

39:14.080 --> 39:17.400
I was working alongside
an SHO colleague

39:17.400 --> 39:19.680
called Shruti Acharya.

39:19.680 --> 39:21.280
Dr Kay...

39:21.280 --> 39:25.280
She asked me to review the patient
in triage,

39:25.280 --> 39:28.440
and then she assisted me
with the caesarean.

39:30.000 --> 39:31.680
Dr Acharya has since...

39:37.760 --> 39:40.480
Dr Acharya has since taken
her own life.

39:42.840 --> 39:44.280
On the morning she died,

39:44.280 --> 39:49.720
Shruti found out she'd passed
her Obs and Gynae membership exams,

39:49.720 --> 39:53.200
exams she worked ridiculously hard
for...

39:54.640 --> 39:56.680
..on top of the 90-hour weeks,

39:56.680 --> 39:58.480
on top of this complaint.

39:59.880 --> 40:03.000
But she didn't see this
as a success.

40:04.840 --> 40:09.120
The idea of carrying on working
in a broken system

40:09.120 --> 40:13.560
under shoddy conditions didn't feel
like any kind of future.

40:16.160 --> 40:17.840
She was a great doctor.

40:20.520 --> 40:23.840
Kind, focused, determined.

40:25.400 --> 40:27.320
And it was still too much for her.

40:31.240 --> 40:33.080
It's too much for anyone.

40:34.560 --> 40:36.560
I mean, you saw what it...

40:36.560 --> 40:38.120
..what it turned me into.

40:41.320 --> 40:44.240
I don't know
if I can do it any more.

40:44.240 --> 40:46.040
Don't leave medicine for me.

40:49.960 --> 40:51.720
One doctor,

40:51.720 --> 40:54.200
in this country,
takes their own life

40:54.200 --> 40:55.760
every three weeks.

40:57.400 --> 41:00.160
And it should be a national fucking
headline every time it happens,

41:00.160 --> 41:02.560
and instead it's just brushed
under the carpet.

41:03.880 --> 41:08.040
Doctors, nurses, midwives,
pharmacists, physios,

41:08.040 --> 41:09.880
a million and a half of them...

41:13.160 --> 41:15.600
..they don't do this
for the money,

41:15.600 --> 41:17.920
for the kudos, for the anything.

41:20.160 --> 41:21.800
They do it because they care.

41:23.040 --> 41:26.000
Day in, day out,
going the extra mile

41:26.000 --> 41:28.240
to keep the rest of us
on the road.

41:28.240 --> 41:31.000
That's a pretty fucking
special thing.

41:33.640 --> 41:37.080
And you could do yourselves a favour
to remember that once in a while.

41:46.280 --> 41:47.680
You know, I...

41:51.320 --> 41:52.680
..I really miss you.

41:58.160 --> 41:59.440
I know.

42:02.360 --> 42:05.080
This is the bit where you say
that you miss me, too.

42:05.080 --> 42:06.520
Yeah, I do.

42:07.920 --> 42:09.560
Well, if you miss me, then...

42:11.400 --> 42:13.520
..let's just...let's...

42:13.520 --> 42:15.320
Why don't we give it another go?

42:16.400 --> 42:17.960
A proper go.

42:19.960 --> 42:21.560
When you get all of me.

42:28.520 --> 42:30.120
But it's what you do.

42:32.480 --> 42:34.320
Being a doctor, it's who you are.

42:35.760 --> 42:37.200
Put your hand on your heart,

42:37.200 --> 42:39.360
and tell me
you want to give all that up.

43:00.560 --> 43:02.120
I don't think I can.

43:07.120 --> 43:08.480
It's OK.

43:14.360 --> 43:15.760
It's OK.

43:32.800 --> 43:34.840
HE SIGHS

43:46.840 --> 43:48.400
WOMAN:  Call an ambulance!

43:48.400 --> 43:50.200
Can't call an ambulance
at a hospital.

43:50.200 --> 43:51.880
Get someone, then!

43:54.000 --> 43:55.520
Hello.

43:55.520 --> 43:57.080
I'm Adam. I'm one of the doctors.

43:57.080 --> 43:59.600
What kind of a doctor?
Doesn't matter what kind!

43:59.600 --> 44:01.040
Right, hello.

44:01.040 --> 44:03.160
Baby's just sitting there,
ready to come out.

44:03.160 --> 44:05.280
Probably best if we finish
what you've started.

44:05.280 --> 44:07.280
Next contraction,
give me a nice big push.

44:07.280 --> 44:09.480
Have you got anything
to put down on the seats?

44:09.480 --> 44:11.640
Oh, is that ever going to come out
of the upholstery?

44:11.640 --> 44:13.760
SHE SCREAMS Honestly, Tim!

44:13.760 --> 44:15.240
Shoelaces.

44:15.240 --> 44:17.560
You're doing so well.
Nearly there. Nearly there.

44:17.560 --> 44:18.800
SHE WHIMPERS

44:18.800 --> 44:20.880
Push, push. Push, push, push!

44:20.880 --> 44:22.520
Here we go.

44:22.520 --> 44:24.600
SHE WAILS

44:24.600 --> 44:26.600
BABY CRIES

44:27.920 --> 44:29.440
Congratulations.

44:30.600 --> 44:31.920
Oh!

44:31.920 --> 44:33.480
Laces.

44:35.680 --> 44:37.520
Something to cut the cord?

44:40.240 --> 44:41.800
Hi.

44:47.160 --> 44:49.000
What do we do now?

44:49.000 --> 44:51.360
I think you have to feed it
for a few years,

44:51.360 --> 44:53.800
let it live in your house,
and then send it to school.

44:55.400 --> 44:58.000
Right, labour ward's
on the second floor

44:58.000 --> 44:59.880
of that building there. Um...

45:01.400 --> 45:03.720
..just give me a minute,
and I'll get you up there.

45:03.720 --> 45:05.560
Thank you so much, Dr...

45:05.560 --> 45:07.600
Adam's a good name.

45:14.400 --> 45:15.600
Oh.

45:15.600 --> 45:16.680
For fuck's sake.

45:17.840 --> 45:19.840
# This is going to sting

45:21.440 --> 45:23.600
# This is going to slay you

45:24.960 --> 45:27.360
# This is going to break your heart

45:28.440 --> 45:30.600
# It's going to tear you apart

45:32.040 --> 45:34.160
# It's going to make
your eyes water

45:35.520 --> 45:38.160
# Oh, it's a major, major trauma

45:39.720 --> 45:41.600
# Yes, this is going to hurt

45:42.680 --> 45:45.560
# Hurt me more than love. #
